            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My experience with Army Public School, Bhopal, has been nothing short of terrible. The level of discrimination between students based on their parents’ backgrounds is appalling. Children of Army officers are given clear advantages, while those from civilian families are treated unfairly—whether in academics, extracurricular activities, or general school interactions. This kind of bias is completely unacceptable in an educational institution that should promote equality and fairness.\n\nThe school’s principal, Seema, seems to run the institution with clear favouritism. Instead of fostering a welcoming and nurturing environment for all students, she exhibits partiality and treats parents and students in a highly unprofessional and dismissive manner. Her attitude towards concerns raised by parents is outright pathetic, making it clear that she has her own set of rules when dealing with people.\n\nA school should be a place of learning, growth, and equal opportunities for all students, but Army Public School, Bhopal, completely fails in this regard. I would strongly advise parents—especially civilians—to think twice before enrolling their children here. Unless drastic changes are made in leadership and policies, this institution will continue to be a place of discrimination and favouritism rather than quality education.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
